Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown; grey core; white inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and beetle symbol. Rounded ends to stamp .
Type series: KT1204 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Name Dionosos. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 201, 26.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0310)
